caption: Exceptional food, service, and ambience. Perfect for a romantic date.
Such a nice spot! We sat in a cabana with the curtains  and it was perfect! Polite and well informed service. The food was delicious. Great date night spot for sure!
We absolutely love Penumbra. Staff & Owner are endearing.
Looking forward to returning with my relatives. The bill was good for how much you get. Food is similar to a place in San Francisco I liked.
Awesome place very romantic and the food is great 👍 can't wait to go back again
Greattt food and service, very romantic
Good food at fair prices. It's a little dark though. Salmon in particular was great
I look forward to a return trip. Prices were good for how much you get.

We came here celebrating our friend's birthday and we all enjoyed the food. We definitely would like to come back and try other dishes. We all shared the dishes; ordered the baked eggplant rolls, arugula salad, linguine al frutti di mare (changed the sauce to white wine sauce), and bianchi and neri pasta. Everything was delicious. I would definitely order the baked eggplant rolls again for my appetizers. Our server was very friendly and knowledgeable and gave us bunch of great tips and recommendations.
The place is really beautiful and romantic, the food is also good, and the service too

Delicious food. Awesome service! And best of all DELICIOUS FOOD. I had a rib eye steak and my wife the pork chops. Appetizers the jalapeño shrimp OMG. I’m not a person to say OMG EITHER. But OMG! A MUST TRY PLACE!
Extraordinary!
Awesome steaks and lobster - so flavorful and delicious!
Awesome flavors!
Great food, excellent service, awesome atmosphere,  great wine super chill-  will definitely go back.
Yummy food and cute wine happy hour on Tues and Wednesdays

I've been coming here since they opened , years ago. It's been consistently tasty and interesting. The owner uses mostly organic produce, and it really tastes fresh. Ask her and she'll proudly show you pictures of the current crop on the farm.
Awesome experience overall, cannot wait to return. Very cozy and romantic atmosphere
Food was great....service was great too.....

This site is my favorite restaurant.  Of all restaurants I know I favor it most. I always suggests to my friends to go to this restaurant. when  I want to go to a fair lunchon, this is the place that comes straight to my mind. exeptionalgorgeous and all sorts of  food and a large list of dishes.trained crew, and nice ambience. In addition to that, the tariff is affordable. I sent my friends to this place with pleasure.
Everything was amazing. The whole experience was great. From food and drinks to service and vibe. I was impressed! Very recommend!
I eat in this spot a lot since I work nearby. I must say their service is always excellent and they keep the spot well organized all the time. Prices are affordable and they serve generous portions.
I simply liked their food. I always get good customer service there. The place is neat and the employees are always super friendly. Will come visit again.

Great atmosphere, great service and the food was top notch. Luis was awesome. Rita the nice, cute owner welcomed us to our private table for 2.  Jalapeño Shrimp, Pork and Ribeye all fantastic.    It's hard in the city to go out and get a nice dinner that fills you up at a reasonable price.    This is not a small plate disaster for that you leave hungry,  quite the opposite.   Flavors have a Latin flare.    I am going back and bringing friends.

This place is really lovely! It looks very small from the front but the back opens up to a huge but intimate space. We got the salmon and the New York strip and both entrees were very good. The complimentary poblano soup is arguably one of the best soups I've ever had. Worth a visit!

The best rib eye I've ever had. The charcuterie was delicious, watch out for the spicy cheese. It only gets stronger. Our waiter Andrii was courteous and accomodating. The cocktails.. Well I love caipirinha, but it was SO potent. Might try the wine next time.

The food was great. Complementary poblano soup warmed my soul. Chacuterie was okay. Steak was awesome. Cooked exactly medium-rare the way I wanted. The owner and the entire staff were super-friendly. The ambiance was very romantic and great for a date, but I think it can be a great for dinner with family/friends too. Awesome wine list too.

I absolutely loved this place. This hidden gem near Humboldt Park is a Latin theme wine bar and restaurant, that's been around for around 4 yrs. I took a date here because it closer to her. When we entered we initially thought the place was dead because of the empty seats and they asked us if we had reservations. Since we didn't our host escorted us to the back where it was more occupied. She lead us to a curtained both. Very nice touch for us. The service was excellent and the food was delicious. We had red wine and chicken (salad and potato cut fries on the side). They also gave use a complimentary cup of potato soup which was good and spicy. We ordered a cheesecake slice and came with a raspberry and raspberry sauce. Very delicious. Pricey but it's Chicago and fine dining. I highly recommend this place and would love to go back.
Food was the best!!!!!

The best part about Penumbra is the privacy. This isn’t a place where you can hear the conversation of the people next to you. Delicious food. The Jalapeño shrimp appetizer is killer. The steak is perfectly cooked and seasoned. They even gave us a complimentary cup of soup at the start of the meal. The truffle cake dessert was gooey and everything you want in a super-chocolatey dessert. The service was perfect. Absolute gem of a restaurant.
Nice environment and food. The restauranorated with t is decbook, which is so nice. Food is also excellent, I love the market fish, it is fresh and tasty. And wonderful music

I went today and I couldn't wait to give a review, this is a hidden gem in Logan Square the whole experience was perfect, the food was delicious, top notch, the service, at front looks like a regular restaurant-bar, but the magical place is behind the exit sign I will definitely going back.
Absolutely love this place and the ambiance is one of a kind. The Lobster is a must have! We've been coming here for 2 years and it never gets old!
Food was excellent. Service was great. The decor inside was very nice
Delicious food no joke.

Very cozy.attentive the food was AMAZING. My husband really enjoyed the steak and everything. The environment felt like home. I would definitely recomnend my friends to this place. The cook and waiter and the owner were out standing..thank you.
Delicious meal and great service. Very quaint inside.❤

My favorite place to dine. The menu is small but that’s what makes it great. You can taste the quality of the food. I was sold when the SALAD tasted amazing. I’ve never had something and not liked it. The homemade ice cream is a must try.
Best date night restaurant in the City!
Wine was good and they offer tastes. Plus, they have an awesome back room!

Top notch establishment. Hospitality was great, from the bartender to the owner's son to the owner. Owner was gracious to give me a tour. It's a sleek, romantic setting with quality, delicious food and drinks. The right place to impress anyone.
The entire experience was exceptional food, ambience, service
Awesome. Love it.

My husband and i went here, unplanned, super last minute for our anniversary.. we live in Hermosa, and we were surprised we came across such a good place. Hermosa/Logan Square is definitely coming up. The food was GREAT. Hubby and I, both got a steak. I got the flat steak and he got the New york. The shrimp was  GREAT appetizer. We went with our 2 year old, if we were to go back, we would try to get a sitter. lol

Excellent neighborhood wine bar with 5 star food. Every time I'm here I feel like I'm at Nobu, or Catch ... This is how good the food is ... On my way yo order me a Sausage pizza now... They have the best Parmesan that they shave fresh for you.

Such a cozy place, staff with a great attitude, awesome charcuterie and cheese plates and really interesting wine flights. Good tunes as well. Perfect date night on a rainy evening! Can't beat the happy hour. Awesome!!!

Just dined there tonight and I must say the setting the service and the food is all excellent!!! Our server (Adam) was amazing and very helpful I had a great time. Thank you guys for the wonderful experience ❤️
Excellent food, music and service!

Rita, the owner is an extremely personable and gracious host. After she greeted us and showed us to a lovely alcove, she told us the charming story of how Penumbra got its name. She advised us on the wine and food and then took her leave. My friends loved the wine she recommended. My salmon was perfectly done with a crispy skin and tender flesh. The mashed potatoes were very tasty with just the right amount of seasoning. My friends both complimented their steaks and said they were very flavorful and cooked perfectly to medium rare. It's a great place for a date or leisurely meal in a dimly lit, quiet and peaceful ambiance.
Great food, we had the steaks, a full bar and great wine.
Food, drinks, ambiance, service all deserve five stars
Amazing food and service!!! Great romantic spot!

Top 5 most romantic restaurants in Chicago. Candles and dimmed lighting, murmered voices, latin love songs at a background volume. Gauzy curtains separating the small intimate tables. Reasonably priced well seasoned dishes artfully presented. A wait staff that genuinely cares about your best experience.  Every year we choose a new romantic restaurant for our anniversary dinner, and this is one of the best.
This place is awesome,  small menu but everything is exquisite, great decor, music & service.
Food was fantastic.  The scallops were great.  The ribeye was fantastic with the chimichurri sauce and the pork was tender and tasty.  It has a great ambiance and is a perfect date dinner spot

When my friend and I when for the first time we got and shared the cheese and meat platter, we highly recommend it. The following time I got the barbecue sandwich with slaw and sweet potato fries, and it was delicious. I can get a bit busy but the service is always been friendly and fast. Can't wait to go again.
Very “homemade” in quality and ambience, not necessarily in a good way
Food is amazing and service is impeccable!

Penumbra is a great little place for a quiet night out, date night or even special occasion.  When you walk in the front of the space seems almost more like a coffee shop, as just the host stand and the bar are situated up there but there was no one sitting at the bar.  They then take you to the back dining room which has a quiet and secluded ambiance.  The menu is not huge but focuses on Latin inspired steak and seafood dishes.  There are a couple vegetarian dishes as well.  Prices are spot on and dishes were super flavorful and cooked to perfection.  Service was very attentive and friendly, and helpful with us newbies as we had questions navigating the menu.

Amazing! A friend recommended we go for a celebration dinner and Penumbra did not disappoint. When we walked in we saw the awards for the “most romantic restaurant” on yelp. We were confused at first because it seemed empty and like a standard restaurant. Then the owner took us back through the front of the restaurant and it was like we entered another world. The light was low and each table had a centerpiece of lights. It was beautifully decorated and we both were in shock and awe.  Our waiter brought us a sipping soup that was absolutely delicious - roasted poblano, potato, caramelized onion, cilantro and cream. I would’ve ordered a large bowl for my meal! We got the New York Strip and Pork Chops. Both were amazing. Mine came with mashed potatoes (in the shape of a heart) and a delicious salad while the pork came with roasted vegetables and potatoes. The ambiance and the food was amazing and affordable. We’ll definitely be back
The atmosphere and food were great along with the service.
My girlfriend and I have visited Penumbra on multiple occasions. Its always exceptional with a great atmosphere, accommodating service, and awesome dishes. A must try!
Great atmosphere (very romantic, yet good for  groups), good food, and amazing service. Very reasonable prices. 100% recomended.
Excellent service , Live music and great food
Excellent food, service and atmosphere! Hidden gem
Beautiful atmosphere, great service and a straightforward menu with thoughtful, handcrafted dishes.

MUST TRY!! PHENOMENAL FOOD! Great ambience; cozy, low key, not loud and obnoxious. I enjoy my experience to the fullest...shout out to Andrii(the bartender) who help me through all my debates and decisions with all his knowledge of the menu. It was my first time here and I'll definitely become a regular. Tried plenty of their dishes, and their seafood is fresh and savory(over all my favorite), that's hard to find. This place is definitely a hidden gem in Logan Square.
First time going on my 1 year anniversary. Waiter was excellent explained everything. Ate Bocaditos and flat iron for her and ribeye for me. Best experience I've had.
Excellent!

My wife and I came here for dinner and the first thing that stood out to me was how affordable it was. The quality of the food was great, wine was good and the atmosphere is very intimate. We will definitely be coming back here.
Really excellent hidden gem of a steak and fish place. Great vibe, very relaxed, romantic but somehow also good for small groups.
Superb food, quality service, excellent atmosphere
Great food and service
Excellent food, and service

Took my bf here for his birthday. It was the perfect dinner. Ambience sets the mood. You walk in and looks small but walking into the back is very romantic. We tried the shrimp appetizer and it was amazing. We each had a steak dinner. My bf didnt think he was going to finish it and before he knew, he cleaned out his plate. We were both impressed with the whole experience. I had a capirhiña and of course it was delicious. We plan on coming back with friends.
Amazing amazing amazing! Every time I have Gone the owners have gone above and beyond to make it a special experience. Reasonably priced for great food

Second time celebrating our anniversary at Penumbra (it was a must). Honestly it has ruined my experience with other restaurants when it comes to their lobster. Its amazing and delicious. Plus it's so romantic, great place to spend with your other half. Also their virgin mojitos are on point. Everything is delicious to my flavor.
The ribeye streak was awesome! The waitress was very welcoming and attentive. The inside looks really nice. I would definitely be back.
Took the love of my life here and she loved it. The food man on man was so on point 👌. The little drink they serve u that is like a 🥑 soup, I can't even explain how amazing it tasted!!
Great place for a date. Very romantic.
The food and drinks are delicious.
Amazing atmosphere and delicious food. Everything was cooked to perfection and the service was 10/10. Have already recommended to friends!
This place is perfect. The food was wonderful, the wine was great, and the service was even better.

Throw out what's on the stove and go here instead. Their food is indescribably good, criminally underpriced, and has the nicest staff you'll ever meet. Seriously, you'll pay $27 for the best steak to ever grace your taste buds. I'd have gladly paid twice what I did, and if you go somewhere else you would but it wouldn't be nearly as good.

Absolutely delicious food and service. Everything was perfect! Coconut mojito, jalapeño creole shrimp, complimentary potatoe poblano soup, flat iron steak, house salad, mashed potatoes and flan were all fantastic! A must try!

Everything was beyond amazing! I can not say enough great things about this place. The owner  was the best and so accommodating. Our waiter was informative and attentive. He payed attention to every detail and gave us the best recommendations. Our food was FANTASTIC! Our amazing waiter recommended the Scallops and Jalapeno shrimp. For the entree we got the Flat Iron steak. Everything was cooked and flavored to perfection. P.s I NEVER write reviews but this place deserves it. It was the perfect date night spot.

Penumbra was a stellar take on a classic American steak house. Everything seems to have an extra spice (not inherently spicy, but full of rich flavors). The interior is decieving, with a romantic back dining room beyond the initial bar. Jonathan was a great waiter this evening and recommended the Jalapeno Shrimp and Nuevo York, both of which were incredibly good. Hands down would have another meal there, especially for a special occasion.
Fantastic place with wonderful food and service!  We had our anniversary dinner here, first time dining here, and so very glad we did!  Planning to return as soon as possible.
Amazing food, great romantic atmosphere and the sweetest staff!

Wonderful food and atmosphere, friendly unobtrusive staff. The front bar area can be a little quiet even as the dining area in back is humming. Appetizers were excellent and everything was special from the small bowl of palate clearing potato leak consommé through the meal. The two different steak  dishes ordered at our table we're excellent and included sides and the salmon was also very tasty. Prices were very reasonable.
The food was very very good !!! Oh my god the New York steak was amazing, and the place so nice! I love it! La comida, el lugar, y la atención de todos fue excelente!
Thr food and the atmosphere was on point. First time here definitely coming back.
I love the ambiance of this restaurant. The staff was attentive and very friendly. And the food...AMAZING! Everything was seasoned so well and perfectly prepared

Servers and owner are so nice and know what they offer very well. The private seating in the back is very romantic, all around a great atmosphere.  Food is all very good, honestly dollar per bite Penumbra is unrivaled in my book. Makes very an affordable, memorable date night.
Service was great and food was awesome!

You might think I’m exaggerating but this is one of the best steaks I’ve ever tried. Food is flavorable, staff is very friendly and welcoming and the atmosphere is so romantic. They have booths surrounded by see-through curtains where you can adjust the level of lighting by a knob. How cool is that?! Definitely going back.

Great ambiance, great cocktails, and great food! We tried the jalapeño shrimp, New York steak, vanilla flan, and several cocktails including the grapefruit old fashioned and pineapple mojito. Everything we tasted was phenomenal. Moreover, the service was phenomenal. We will definitely be coming back.
Had a wonderful date night. Being from out of town, I wanted a neighborhood restaurant and not an expensive chain downtown. I got great food at a good price, and a romantic experience.
Perfect. The food was amazing, the cocktails are delicious, and the atmosphere was romantic. Our server, Sebastian, was helpful and diligent. We will be returning.

This restaurant was recommend by my co-worker.. Wow! If you are into romance, this is the spot.. Great menu... the food was outstanding!! The music was dead on awesome.. the environment was even better!   I recommend this restaurant with high 5! The waiter was very friendly and very detail of the menus and ingredients.. The owner, was kind and so nice to talk too. She defiantly knows what romance is!! One more thing... You and your Love one won't be disappointed one bit!! Defiantly going back!!!
Everything was very very good. The Nuevo steak was fantastic and the chocolate desert was amazing. Super great service, especially Salvador, very nice atmosphere too!
Great romantic atmosphere.  Good food.  Great presentation.
Not much to say. Interesting presentation and average taste. Great staff members!

My fiancé and I went to this restaurant based on the recommendation from a friend.  It was absolutely amazing.   The ambiance was perfect and the food was incredibly delicious!   I recommend this restaurant without hesitation.
Love this place. Relaxing. Awesome food and service. Friendly people

Great place for a special occasion, or especially for a date. The atmosphere is amazing, the seating is very comfortable. You get treated great! Incredible hospitality! The food is perfect and delicious. They also have a wonderful drink selection. I highly recommend this place!!!
Great jalapeno margarita

Recommended by a friend. Scallops cooked perfect. Flat iron steak was cooked as ordered with a favorable seasoning. Very friendly staff and excellent service. The restaurant was surprisingly empty for a Friday evening. A great option if you want to avoid lines at trending spots.
Nice Ambiance, Good Food, Attentive Wait Staff, Pleasant Background Music.

My husband chose Penumbra for my 30th birthday dinner based on the reviews and we were NOT disappointed. It's a small and unassuming restaurant front and when we entered, we were met with a huge group of people participating in the free wine tasting. We were led to the back of the restaurant which opened up into a beautiful and dimly lit room with curtains and cabanas and dining tables. They start you off with complimentary soup and we shared the crab cake appetizer which was delicious. I got the New York steak entree and my husband got the pork, both of which were delicious! We finished off with the coconut flan which was thick and creamy and amazing!! Our server Sebastian was excellent and prompt. He drew a rose with chocolate sauce and wrote happy birthday on our dessert plate. We met the owner and she was so sweet and nice. We loved our visit and we definitely will be back!
Good food and ambiance.
The guy playing the marimbas is THE MAN!!!

(Translated by Google) Looking for where to spend some time in Fullerton we find this pleasant surprise. Except for the curtains that do not reveal the beauty of the bar at the entrance, everything was perfect. Without a doubt it is a recommended site. The food, very good. Excellent service. Decoration not to my liking but it is different.  (Original) Buscando donde pasar un rato en Fullerton nos encontramos con esta agradable sorpresa. Salvo las cortinas que no dejan ver la belleza del bar que está a la entrada, todo fue a la perfección. Sin duda que es un sitio recomendable. La comida, muy buena. Servicio excelente. Decoración no a mi gusto pero es distinta.

Lovely place, with a very intimate feel.  Perfect for a date night.  Each table for 2 (called "cabanas" by the hostess) is surrounded by a thin veil, which is nice and provides a bit of privacy.  The flat iron steak and accompanying salad were delicious.  Potatoes were ok.
The food and server was awesome. I really liked the place. Atmosphere was really cool. And it wasn’t so expensive i got so nice food with a reasonable price!!
Romantic, well priced... seafood and steaks, wine.. all that is good in life
Excellent food and service - much more than the storefront would indicate.

Super cool hidden gem! Delicious meat and cheese tray, wine and steak. And they started us with a free sample of their soup which was scrumptious. Overall a cool experience. Dark and romantic in the back.
I love Penumbra. It’s a hidden gem and a local favorite. The food is always outstanding as well as the service. Check it out if you haven’t!

Found by accident. Great surprise! Unassuming entrance a bit hard to see sign outside. Once inside opens up to back room with excellent decor. Really excellent service. Good was amazing. Went with a large group and everything was to perfection. A must try. Great little private dining areas for couples with long flowing curtains.  Will definitely visit again. Nice addition to Logan swuare
Friendly place and good food. Creole shrimp is delicious
Seek this place out. Top notch food and service.
Just incredible. Went with two others and each of us raved over all three dishes. Service was excellent, very cozy atmosphere, meals prepared with care and cooked perfectly.
What an unexpected delight! Cute little restaurant with DELICIOUS FOOD. Four stars because we always wait so long for the check to come after we are done eating. :(
Delicious food, great wine selection. A warm staff and romantic environment that also manages to be reasonably priced. We love Penumbra! Truly a special place.

The term "hidden gem" is so overused that it's basically lost all meaning for me. But this place really does match that. The front room is a very standard bar with a few small tables, but the back room is an intimate space with secluded alcoves and some nice tables.  Our night started off perfectly with great service from Sebastian who did a wonderful job of suggesting three different wine options for me and my fiancée based on our preferences. He absolutely nailed it with a nice Malbec, that satisfied our very disparate tastes.  We ordered a half portion of the charcuterie with our wine and this was a great way to start things off, alongside a small (complimentary!) portion of a nice homemade soup.
Amazing food, family restaurant. Highly recommend. Salvador and his mom are amazing. Steak was cooked to perfection
After you get over the fact that your server has to hand you a flashlight to read the menu, the food is very good and the drinks are well made. Great intimate spot for dinner with a special someone.
Hidden neighborhood Gem. Great food and drinks. The front bar is upscale and back room has a great classy relaxed feel to it.
Great food and excellent service. Would definitely recommend.

Penumbra has been one of our favorite go-to places in Logan Square since they opened. We call it Shrimp House because they have the best shrimp. The Creole Jalapeño shrimp is the best shrimp I've ever had. It's also got such good flavor and great heat.  The atmosphere makes you feel at home and the staff are all great. The owner always takes such good care of us. We love her!

My family and I went here to celebrate my Dad's 60th birthday.  In total we had 5 cocktails, a bottle of wine, 6 steak dinners, and two shareable deserts for around $250.  The steaks were well seasoned/cooked and the desert was delicious.  They even wrote a birthday message to my dad and put some candles on the cake, which was a nice touch.  Additionally the restaurant was fairly quiet, which was nice as we were able to have a good conversation between the 6 of us.  We had a great time at a reasonable price and I would highly recommend trying it out.
One of the best meals I've had in Chicago. Great service and beautiful setting. It is dark inside, but they give you miniature flashlights to read the menu.

I really didn't care for it at all. Seemed like all the dishes were thinly veiled repeats of each other. Almost all the steaks had roasted garlic peppercorn...most dishes were served with avocado cream. The steaks were not very good...seemed like the cheapest cuts with a chewed up texture. Flat iron was cooked closer to MW than MR. I guess that's why entrees can be kept in the $20-range rather than $40-50. Waitress was fairly snarky. Wine guy was however terrifically knowledgeable and they had a well rounded and affordable wine list. And finally, if you gotta offer flashlights to read the menu, it stands to reason that your guests also can't really see what they're eating. Deliberate?

We have come to Penumbra almost every other week since the first time we came and loved it and I have to say that every single time we have received the same great service. We always ask for Sebastian (our waiter) and the food... wow just delicious! The atmosphere is also super nice and romantic. We came last night again to celebrate my aunts birthday and even the owner came to great us and thank us for coming in again. Wow out of hundreds of people she gets she remembered us. Great place all around.
Ribeye medium-rare was done perfectly. Very tasty with the garlic. My fiance had the Salmon and also very awesome.
The food was great. The service was excellent and the staff are very friendly and take care of the customers well.
Best hidden gem in Logan Square.

The waiter (Sebastian) was phenomenal-very attentive.  The owner came out and greeted us.  Everyone in our group had ribeyes that were cooked perfectly.  We had chocolate cake for desert. It was amazing.  I highly recommend.
A yelp reviewer described it perfectly when saying it is a hidden gem

Very beautiful decor. There is music playing, beautifully, but not loud enough so that you can't hear the other person you're with talking. The food was excellent. Steak was on point and the potatoes were decorated so well and exceptional.
We had an excellent experience here! Fantastic wine! Excellent charcuterie plate! Excellent service!
Delicious entrees (I tried 3 of them!).  and relaxing atmosphere.   Great service!
Best dinner and Romantic

This place was amazing. It feels very welcoming and the food was phenomenal. They do not shy away from spice and all the meat was cooked perfectly. We ordered the shrimp appetizer based on yelp recommendations and it was really good. Come and try this place. We are big foodies and will definitely be back

If you aren't careful you may walk right past this place. That would be a real shame because Penumbra has a chance to be a real gem in the neighborhood. We were greeted by the owners at the door. The interior is clean and intimate with a surprisingly expansive and well appointed back room.  The steak was nearly perfectly cooked. Vegetables were also nearly perfectly grilled. They brought a potato soup sample that was delicious with a bit of spice. Don't miss out on the poblano mashed potatoes - they were a delicious side dish.  We were very impressed with the entire experience and will be back soon!

The food was excellent! Everyone thoroughly enjoyed their appetizer and entrée.  The service was friendly and attentive.  The inside of the restaurant looks much nicer than the outside of the building. I would definitely recommend Penumbra and plan on returning soon!
Came for a birthday party for 4 and had an intimate experience. The service was on point without being overbearing. Food was excellent. Can't wait to come back for a drink in the front part.
